title.narrative: OUTPUT 2.2: QUALITY BASIC EDUCATION

description.narrative: By the end of 2020, 25,000 children in 5 districts access and complete quality basic education with improved learning outcomes, which contributes to Disaster Risk Reduction, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning And Child-Friendly Schools, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, children, especially the most disadvantaged children, benefit from inclusive, quality early learning and basic education with improved learning outcomes attained.

description.narrative: UNICEF efforts in 2020 largely focused on the response to closure of schools due to the COVID-19 pandemic, providing support to distance learning and advocating and supporting early reopening of schools and to restore learning safely. UNICEF continued to provide technical leadership to the education sector response to COVID-19 and supported the Ministry of Education, Youth and Sports (MoEYS) in coordination of efforts among the local education partners.; | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
